ğŸ“Œ Prerequisites

Before starting, make sure you have:

AWS Account with sufficient permissions

An EC2 instance (Amazon Linux / Ubuntu recommended)

IAM role attached to EC2 with:

EKS

EC2

IAM

VPC

ELB permissions

ğŸ”§ Step 1: Install Required Tools on EC2
1ï¸âƒ£ Install AWS CLI
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o awscliv2.zip
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install
aws --version

2ï¸âƒ£ Install kubectl
curl -O https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/amazon-eks/1.29.0/2024-01-04/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/
kubectl version --client

3ï¸âƒ£ Install eksctl
curl --silent --location "https://github.com/weaveworks/eksctl/releases/latest/download/eksctl_Linux_amd64.tar.gz" | tar xz
sudo mv eksctl /usr/local/bin
eksctl version

â˜¸ï¸ Step 2: Create EKS Cluster Using eksctl
eksctl create cluster \
  --name netflix-cluster \
  --region ap-south-1 \
  --nodegroup-name netflix-nodes \
  --node-type t3.medium \
  --nodes 2 \
  --nodes-min 1 \
  --nodes-max 3 \
  --managed


â³ This takes 10â€“15 minutes.

Verify cluster:

kubectl get nodes

ğŸ” Step 3: Associate IAM OIDC Provider (Security Best Practice)
eksctl utils associate-iam-oidc-provider \
  --region ap-south-1 \
  --cluster netflix-cluster \
  --approve

ğŸ³ Step 4: Build Netflix-Style Docker Image
Sample Dockerfile (Production-ready)
FROM node:16-alpine AS build
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install
COPY . .
RUN npm run build

FROM nginx:alpine
COPY --from=build /app/build /usr/share/nginx/html
EXPOSE 80
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]


Build image:

docker build -t netflix-app .


Tag & push to Docker Hub (or ECR):

docker tag netflix-app <your-dockerhub-username>/netflix:latest
docker push <your-dockerhub-username>/netflix:latest

ğŸ“¦ Step 5: Create Kubernetes Deployment

netflix-deployment.yml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: netflix-deployment
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: netflix
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: netflix
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: netflix
        image: <your-dockerhub-username>/netflix:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80


Apply:

kubectl apply -f netflix-deployment.yml
kubectl get pods

ğŸŒ Step 6: Expose Application Using LoadBalancer

netflix-service.yml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: netflix-service
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: netflix
  ports:
    - port: 80
      targetPort: 80


Apply:

kubectl apply -f netflix-service.yml
kubectl get svc

ğŸš€ Step 7: Access Netflix-Style UI

Get external URL:

kubectl get svc netflix-service


Open in browser:

http://<EXTERNAL-IP>


ğŸ‰ Netflix-style frontend is now live on AWS EKS.

